Hi All,

I installed php pact foundation package inside my docker container and when running my verify consumer test:
    #[Test]
    public function testPactVerifyConsumer()
    {
        $config = new VerifierConfig();
        $config->getProviderInfo()
            ->setName('my-service')
            ->setHost('http://host.docker.internal')
            ->setPort(8080);
        $config->getProviderState()
            ->setStateChangeUrl(new Uri(<my_url>)));

        $verifier = new Verifier($config);
        $verifier->addFile(__DIR__ . '<path to contract file>');

        $verifyResult = $verifier->verify();

        $this->assertTrue($verifyResult);
    }
}
But i get error bin/pact-ffi-lib/pact.so file not found. after insalling ffi i get bin/pact-ffi-lib/pact.so: invalid ELF header
Here is the package file causing this:

    public static function getLibrary(): string
    {
        $extension = PHP_OS_FAMILY === 'Windows' ? 'dll' : (PHP_OS === 'Darwin' ? 'dylib' : 'so');

        return self::$destinationDir . "/bin/pact-ffi-lib/pact.{$extension}";
    }
how to solve this issue?

Thanks in advance

Here is how we instantiate Verifier:
```php
$client = new Client();
$client->call('pactffi_log_to_stderr', 4);
$verifier = new Verifier($verifierConfig, client: $client);
```

This stopped working, because `call` function was made private in d8f50a90528a667e4a2e7c263f9c5f1965c26bdc

